EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Assembly to pass A.2242, which would amend the Real Property Tax Law to provide that the definition of income be offset by any unreimbursed medical and prescription drug expenses paid by a senior citizen for purposes of determining eligibility for Senior Citizen Rent Increase Exemption (SCRIE) benefits, and further urging the New York State Senate to introduce and pass a companion bill.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the construction and maintenance of private sewers.
EventItemMatterName: Construction and maintenance of private sewers.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of the Domestic Defense Fund Act of 2005, sponsored by Senator Hillary Clinton, which aims to increase the flow of Homeland Security funds directly to local communities.
EventItemMatterName: Domestic Defense Fund Act of 2005, Support

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the board of elections notifying city residents who voted by affidavit or paper ballot as to whether or not their vote was tallied, and if not, provide a reason.
EventItemMatterName: Board of elections notifying city residents who voted by affidavit or paper ballot as to whether or not their vote was tallied.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the composition of the fire department pension fund medical board.
EventItemMatterName: Composition of the fire department pension fund medical board.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city administrative code, in relation to the sale of toy or imitation identification badges and/or shields.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of toy or imitation identification badges and/or shields.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting the concept of the Underground Railroad Curriculum, a culturally relevant and inspiring educational tool that educates students about the contributions, accomplishments and struggles of African Americans.
EventItemMatterName: Supporting the concept of the Underground Railroad Curriculum.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to disclosure in advertising with respect to theatre show times.
EventItemMatterName: Disclosure in advertising with respect to theatre show times.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution honoring the life and achievements of actor and activist Ossie Davis.
EventItemMatterName: Honoring the life and achievements of actor and activist Ossie Davis.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the definition of campaign contribution under the Campaign Finance Law.
EventItemMatterName: Definition of campaign contribution under the Campaign Finance Law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to developing a watershed protection plan for the watershed/sewershed of Jamaica Bay.
EventItemMatterName: Developing a watershed protection plan for the watershed/sewershed of Jamaica Bay.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to create a temporary task force to study the feasibility of transferring city-owned wetlands to the jurisdiction of the department of parks and recreation.
EventItemMatterName: Create a temporary task force to study the feasibility of transferring city-owned wetlands to the jurisdiction of the department of parks and recreation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to developing a comprehensive program for the remediation and reuse of brownfields.
EventItemMatterName: Developing a comprehensive program for the remediation and reuse of brownfields.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution strongly urging the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation to immediately develop and implement a total maximum daily load for nitrogen pollution into Jamaica Bay in order to preserve and protect this New York City jewel possessing exceptional ecological diversity.
EventItemMatterName: Develop and implement a total maximum daily load for nitrogen pollution into Jamaica Bay.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Legislature of the State of New York to expand the state Hate Crimes Law (Penal Law Article 485) to include bias motivated crime that is not directed at a particular person or location.
EventItemMatterName: Expand the state Hate Crimes Law (Penal Law Article 485)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel and the best available technology for reducing the emission of pollutants by diesel fuel-powered private ferries.
EventItemMatterName: Use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel by diesel fuel-powered private ferries.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel and the best available technology for reducing the emission of pollutants by diesel fuel-powered ferries owned by, operated by or on behalf of, or leased by the city.
EventItemMatterName: Use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel by diesel fuel-powered ferries owned by, operated by or on behalf of, or leased by the city.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing the penalties for the unlawful use of police uniforms, badges or emblems.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing penalties for the unlawful use of police uniforms, badges or emblems.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Bush Administration to abandon its efforts to dismantle the current social security system.
EventItemMatterName: Bush Administration to abandon its efforts to dismantle the current social security system.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the charter of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Mayor’s Management Report to report on the allocation of funds and provision of services for each agency, where applicable, geographically by census tract, zip code, community district, council district and borough.
EventItemMatterName: MMR to report on the allocation of funds and provision of services for each agency, where applicable.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting S.11, the “Standing With Our Troops Act of 2005,” and calling upon the United States Senate to pass said bill and for the House of Representatives to introduce and pass similar legislation.
EventItemMatterName: Supporting the “Standing With Our Troops Act of 2005” (S.11)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Transit Authority to set a maximum safe speed for trains entering stations.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Transit Authority to set a maximum safe speed for trains entering stations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States House of Representatives and the United States Senate to enact legislation increasing the amount of the “military death gratuity” from approximately $12,000 to $100,000, and urging the President of the United States to sign such legislation into law.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the amount of the “military death gratuity” from approximately $12,000 to $100,000.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the charter of the city of New York, in relation to ensuring that eligible pre-trial detainees are allowed to register to vote and vote by absentee ballot.
EventItemMatterName: Ensuring that eligible pretrial detainees are allowed to register to vote and vote by absentee ballot.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the appropriate committee of the City Council to hold a hearing on the impact of the Department of Education Superintendent Suspension Sites on schools that house such sites, including concerns regarding increased criminal incidents within the schools and surrounding neighborhoods, the academic placement of suspended students, and the adequacy of education for suspended students.
EventItemMatterName: Impact of the Department of Education Superintendent Suspension Sites.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging Mayor Michael Bloomberg to instruct the City Law Department to withdraw the appeal of Judge Doris Ling-Cohan’s decision in the case of Hernandez v. Robles, and instruct the Clerk of the City of New York to comply with the sum and substance of that decision by issuing a civil marriage license to any and every same-sex couple that is otherwise qualified to receive such license.
EventItemMatterName: City Law Dep't to withdraw the appeal of Judge Doris Ling-Cohan’s decision in the case of Hernandez v. Robles.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Millman A.1861, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the repair, construction and maintenance of athletic fields in the city of New York”
EventItemMatterName: AN ACT, repair, construction and maintenance of NYC athletic fields (A.1861).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright A.764, “An Act to amend the parks, recreation and historic law, in relation to vacating a trust.
EventItemMatterName: Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation Law (A.764)

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Dilan S.1081 and Assembly Member Robinson A.2014, “AN ACT authorizing the city of New York to reconvey its interest in certain real property acquired by in rem tax foreclosure in the borough of Brooklyn to former owner George Black, or if he is deceased, to the person or persons who would have inherited said property from him or to their successor in interest, notwithstanding expiration of the two year period within which application may be made to the city to release its interest in property thus acquired; Block No. 1762, Lot No. 62 on tax map for the borough of Brooklyn.”
EventItemMatterName: In Rem, George Black, Brooklyn

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Sabini S. 1246 and Assembly Member Lafayette A.2063, “An Act in relation to the control and stabilization of rents and rental agreements in certain retail commercial space in cities having a population of more than one million.”
EventItemMatterName: AN ACT, relating to the control and stabilization or rent and rental agreements in certain retail commercial spaces in cities with one million or more. (S.1246, A.2063)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Standards and Ethics
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the annual disclosure of financial interests by certain officers and employees of the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Annual disclosure of financial interests by certain officers and employees of the city of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing the penalties for the unlawful use or possession of official police cards.
